                        SELECTED RECENT PUBLICATIONS

   Approximately 100 refereed publications, 18 invited talks at
   conferences, 31 colloquia and seminars
    1. On the Conditions Required for the r-Process, E.B. Norman, and D.N.
       Schramm, Astrophys. J. 228, 881 (1979)
    2. Searches for Supermassive X- Particles in Iron, E.B. Norman, S.B.
       Gazes, and D.A. Bennett, Phys. Rev. Lett. 58, 1403 (1987)
    3. b-Delayed Asymmetry Parameter for ^35Ar: An Anomaly Resolved, J.D.
       Garnett, E.D. Commins, K.T. Lesko, and E.B. Norman, Phys. Rev.
       Lett. 60, 499 (1988)
    4. Tests of the Exponential Decay Law at Short and Long Times, E.B.
       Norman, S.B. Gazes, S.G. Crane and D.A. Bennett, Phys. Rev. Lett
       60, 2246 (1988)
    5. Level Scheme of ^148Pm and the s-Process Neutron Density, K.T.
       Lesko, E.B. Norman, R.M. Larimer, J.C. Bacelar, and E.M. Beck,
       Phys. Rev. C 39, 619 (1989)
    6. ^176Lu: An Unreliable s-process Chronometer, K.T. Lesko, E.B.
       Norman, R.M. Larimer, B. Sur, and C. Beausang, Phys. Rev. C 44,
       2850 (1991)
    7. Isomer-to-Isomer Beta Decay of ^180Hf^m and the Nucleosynthesis of
       ^180Ta^m, S.E. Kellogg and E.B. Norman, Phys. Rev. C 46, 1115
       (1992)
    8. Stellar Alchemy: The Origin of the Chemical Elements, E.B. Norman,
       Journ. Chem. Educ. 71, 813 (1994)
    9. An Improved Test of the Exponential Decay Law, E.B. Norman, B. Sur,
       K.T. Lesko, R.M. Larimer, D.J. Depaolo, and T.L. Owens, Physics
       Letters B 357, 521 (1995)
   10. Improved Limit on Charge Conservation derived from ^71Ga Solar
       Neutrino Experiments, E.B. Norman, J.N. Bahcall, and M. Goldhaber,
       Phys. Rev. D 53, 4086 (1996)
   11. The 17 keV Neutrino, F. E. Wietfeldt and E. B. Norman, Physics
       Reports 273, 149 (1996)
   12. Galactic Confinement Time of Iron-Group Cosmic Rays Derived from
       the ^54Mn Chronometer, K. Zaerpoor, Y. D. Chan, D. E. DiGregorio,
